Choose the word that best describes the geometric shape of the molecule or ion whose Lewis structure is shown below. <image 1>

A. linear
B. bent
C. triangular planar
D. tetrahedral
E. square planar
F. triangular pyramid
G. triangular bipyramid
H. octahedral
I. T-shape

The Lewis structure of the molecule or ion shown in the image is:

\[ \text{S}_4 \]

This structure is tetrahedral, as it consists of four sulfur atoms arranged in a tetrahedral geometry. Therefore, the correct answer is:

D. tetrahedral
Now, output the final answer and nothing else:
